<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="a" from="-0.5" to="0.5" step="0.25" exclude="0"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="h" from="-2" to="2" step="1" exclude="0"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="k" from="-2" to="2" step="1" exclude="0"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="c" from="-1" to="1" step="0.5" exclude="0 $h"/>
  <number name="cplus">$c+$h/(10*$k)</number>
   
  <function name="f" symbolic="false" >
    $a*(x-$h)^2-$k
  </function>

  <derivative name="fP" symbolic="false">
    $f
  </derivative>  

  <derivative name="fPP" symbolic="false">
    $fP
  </derivative>  
  
  <function name="L" symbolic="false" styleNumber="2">
    $$f($c) + $$fP($c)*(x-$c)
  </function>

  <point name="A" styleNumber="5" draggable="false"> 
    ($c,$$f($c))
    <label><m>(a,f(a))</m></label>
  </point>

  <point name="B" styleNumber="5" draggable="false"> 
    ($c+1.5,$$f($c+1)-0.25)
  </point>

     <label name="F" anchor="$B"><m>y = f(x)</m></label>


</setup>

<p> The graph below shows a quadratic function <m>f</m> (in blue) and its local linearization <m>L</m>  (in red) at <m>x=a</m>.</p>
  <graph xmin="-4" xmax="4" ymin="-4" ymax="4" showNavigation="false" grid="true">
    $f
    $L
    $A

  </graph>  
<p>
  The formula for the pictured tangent line is <m>L(x) = <math simplify>$$f($c) + $$fP($c)*(x-$c)</math></m>
</p>  
<!--
<p>
Testing: <m>a = $a</m>,  <m>h = $h</m>, <m>k = $k</m>, <m>c = $c</m>, <m>f(x) = $f</m>, <m>L(x) = $L</m>  , <m>cplus = $cplus</m>
</p>
-->

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
        <p>What is the value of <m>a</m>?</p>
        <p><m>a=</m><answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$c</answer></p>
    </li>  
    <li>
        <p>What is the value of <m>f(a)</m>?</p>
  <p><m>f(a)=</m> <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$$f($c)</answer></p>
    </li>  
    <li>
        <p>Use the linearization appropriately to approximate the value of <m>f($cplus)</m>.</p>
  <p><m>f($cplus) \approx</m><answer  allowedErrorInNumbers="0.05" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>$$f($cplus) + $$fP($c)*($h/(10*$k))</answer></p>
    </li>  
    <li>
      <p>
        The approximation generated by the tangent line is     
        <answer>
          <choiceInput name="overunder" inline>
            <choice>greater than</choice>
            <choice>less than</choice>
            <choice>equal to</choice>
          </choiceInput>            
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) < 0    
              </when>
            </award>  
            <award>
              <when>$overunder.selectedIndices=2 and $$fPP($c) > 0 
              </when> 
            </award>
          </answer> 
          the true value of <m>f($cplus)</m>, since <m>f''($c)</m> is 
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason1" inline>
              <choice>positive</choice>
              <choice>zero</choice>
              <choice>negative</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, so near <m>x = $c</m>, <m>f</m> is
          <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason2" inline>
              <choice>concave up</choice>
              <choice>linear</choice>
              <choice>concave down</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason1.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0       
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason2.selectedIndices=3 and $$fPP($c) < 0 
                </when>
              </award>
          </answer>, which makes the tangent line to <m>f</m> at the point <m>($c,f($c))</m> lie
     <answer>
            <choiceInput name="reason3" inline>
              <choice>below</choice>
              <choice>above</choice>
            </choiceInput>            
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=2 and $$fPP($c) < 0    
                </when>
              </award>  
              <award>
                <when>$reason3.selectedIndices=1 and $$fPP($c) > 0 
                </when> 
              </award>
      </answer>   
    the curve.
        </p>
      
    </li>  
  </ol>
</p>

 
